This daemon seems to ignore most of the existing code we have that already does a majority of these generic operations (read a config file, read a gpio, etc).

Please familiarize yourself with how entity-manager reactors are intended to work, and rewrite this application appropriately.
Already replied here https://gerrit.openbmc.org/c/openbmc/dbus-sensors/+/75617/comment/43f98d8e_95ea172f/. So marking this comment as resolved for now as comments are related.
remove.  Using namespace is against the coding standard.
Done

Using coroutines means that basically all the utility functions available for reactors are now not usable in a coroutine.  That doesn't really seem workable at this point, unless you're planning on reworking all the utils classes to support both coroutine and not?

> Using coroutines means that basically all the utility functions available for reactors are now not usable in a coroutine.  That doesn't really seem workable at this point, unless you're planning on reworking all the utils classes to support both coroutine and not?

As per our discussion on discord and in LeakDetector PR, Meta will be contributing new daemons based on coroutines. During this development process, we are also creating common classes and interfaces that can be reused across these new daemons. For future, we can plan to migrate the existing daemons to the new code flow.
Please look at and understand how entity manager reactors are intended to operate.  This daemon appears to have ignored basically all the existing things.
Already replied here https://gerrit.openbmc.org/c/openbmc/dbus-sensors/+/75617/comment/43f98d8e_95ea172f/. So marking this comment as resolved for now as comments are related.

We already have things that can monitor gpios without this dependency.  I don't really want to add it here unless there's a holistic plan, ideally in a design doc documenting:
1. Why taking the new dependency is required.
2. How the new dependency is going to be rolled out.

I suppose here you are referring to adding PDI as a dependency. If yes, then as per our discussion on other threads - Meta will be contributing new daemons based on coroutines and PDI. I have also covered some details on this thread about migration https://gerrit.openbmc.org/c/openbmc/dbus-sensors/+/75617/comment/43f98d8e_95ea172f/.
Updated the cable monitor code based on comments in LeakDetector.
